34. Cancer Discov. 2018 Apr;8(4):OF5. doi: 10.1158/2159-8290.CD-NB2018-016. Epub 2018Feb 20.BMI Can Underestimate Breast Cancer Risk.[No authors listed]New findings suggest that postmenopausal women with high levels of body fat areat increased risk of ER-positive breast cancer, even if their body mass index is within the normal range. If confirmed, these results would put many more women atelevated risk for breast cancer than was previously thought, with implicationsfor the way that healthy-weight women should be counseled to reduce their health risks.Â©2018 American Association for Cancer Research.DOI: 10.1158/2159-8290.CD-NB2018-016 PMID: 29463507 